FUCK LIVE JOURNAL. I'M MOVING ONCE AGAIN.

Well, it's officially fall. The first cold front of the season has made it's grand entrance and I'm extremely ecstatic!. I'm sitting here at the Union gazing out the window and listening to Jens Lekman on my iPod while the front puffs around lifeless autumn leaves which are now accumulating onto the ground. The traces of caffeine in my veins along with the lingering taste of coffee, my music, and the morphing weather are giving me a sense of euphoria. Even the ants crawling around on my table seem to be happy with me!
OMGWTF?!! I HAVEN'T BEEN HERE IN AGES

Chiptunes make me feel all warm and fuzzy inside. They take me back to my happy childhood days with my Game Gear, Sega Genesis and even my uncle's ancient Atari 2600. I suppose that is why I openly welcome electronic driven beepbeepbleepbloopiness. It's my everlasting love with technology. Oh LOL! Remember in high school when I used to be a little wannabe mod? Yeah, those days are over. I grew up. No more Motown, no more the Who, no more I wanna Vespa, and no more bobbed hair-cuts. I look back at that little phase I went through and how I was so passionate about it and laugh. It was stupid and so teenage. I am also not crazy about the Beatles anymore. The Beatles have been replaced with Kraftwerk. My dad would hate to hear me say this and he might quite possibly kill me. I love Kraftwerk way more than the Beatles. I'm not saying the Beatles are crap! It's just that the Beatles don't really mean anything to me anymore. Kraftwerk's main drive is technology, and I love technology like I said before. It's just natural for me to choose Kraftwerk over the Beatles. This probably sounds like pointless crap to you guys. Hahah!
I don't want to work today.

Oh LOL! They are clearly not enjoying themselves. This has to be one of the silliest playbacks ever, and check out the geriatric audience! I love how Florian (guy at far right) basically does nothing but glares creepily at the camera, especially around 00:38

Yeah, I'm a big Kraftwerk fan girl. I woulda made da german babiez wit dem back in da 70s and 80s. y que? sheeeeit

I went to the McAllen mall by myself today. It was boring. :( BUT THOSE DAMN EURO-MEXICAN BOYS ARE EVERYWHERE!!
I did some damage. I bought myself a lacoste polo and jacket at, mind you, Joe Brand. That shit ain't cheap!

I then checked out the PetsMart in McAllen to see if they had anything that I would need for my fishies and that wasn't boring. It was cute. They have so many cute fishies!

commuting to edinburg for university + attending classes practically all day + working my ass off and dealing with douche bags at quizno's = exhaustion x_x

I WILL SURVIVE!!

I finally found <lj user="enraged_spork"> on campus. I no longer have to mope around and look lonely at Pan-Am. Yay!

My first day at pan-am was pretty good apart from the shitty parking. It took me nearly 20 minutes to find a parking space. I was sad. It was a great feeling driving buzzed off of homemade hazelnut coffee while listening to Die Mensch Maschine. I have a love affair with Kraftwerk and coffee. On my way home the stupid subliminal McDonald billboards lured me into their trap with their fat ass imagery of Big Macs and fries. I had to pick up a Big Mac and some fries in Harlingen because the images were branded into...my SOUL!. And now I feel guilty after eating my meal. So, I think that should be the last time I'll ever drive on an empty stomach...DAMN YOU MCDONALD'S!! I work today and my manager is back, so work is pretty much going to return to being craptastic again.

I swear, Rick the creepy co-worker acts bizarre. He was taking the trash out the front entrance which makes no sense since we have a door at the back of the store that is close to the dumpster. We have that back door for a reasons and one of them is for taking out the trash! I asked him why he wouldn't simply use back the door, and he came up with an illogical response. "Uhhh, I just don't want it to make it seem like I'm taking anything that I shouldn't be taking, ya know? especially with the manager not being around." I said, "ok, but that doesn't make any sense." He said, "ya know Ana, you just gotta play it safe." I thought, "wtf?" I really wanted to say, "why would anyone think you're stealing anything, you're taking out the trash! going out the front door with bags makes you look more suspicious than going out the back, dumb ass!!" But I didn't argue with him, because he clearly didn't know what the hell he was taking about. He also goes to the restroom way too much than normal. I know he goes to drink alcohol because he comes back and smells like it, and I already discussed this with the owner. I WORK WITH A BUNCH OF ALCOHOLIC DUMB ASSES and it's unsettling.nu I'm off today so I'm going shopping for some new shirts at the Mercedes outlet mall with my mom. ouais.

I got a newer, and better blog.

http://anananana.wordpress.com/

please do visit. It'll make me happy.

I bought 4 male red-blonde guppies today at PetsMart after my exams as a treat for myself after surviving a second year of craptastic-ness at TSTC. I purchased a small aquarium, two plant decorations, a little bag of stones and cute ancient Greek pillars to go along with the set-up. The fishies are sooo adorable and have been swimming around happily in their new home. I named them Florian, Ralf, Fritz and Henning. Uh huh, I named them after the German 1970s-80s techno pioneers from Kraftwerk. Y que?

I had a crappy day at work last night...again. The register was malfuctioning (it didn't want to open) and we couldn't get a new roll of printing paper to feed into the credit card terminal in the middle of a customer rush. We also ran out of change from the register and I couldn't open the safe to get more because I don't have the authorization to do so. I had to call the manager and he sent his sancha over to help us out. I was embarrassed and a bit stressed out over the problem, but she told me that it was no problem and not to worry about it. I worked with the owner's brother-in-law and he saw me work my hardest that night. He's the reason why the owner's like me so much. He usually brags about my work ethic and how I always am at my best. Soo, mad props to myself.

We also made an ass load of money last night.

I went to my Quizno's today immediately after my exams because I hadn't eaten anything prior and I was craving a honey mustard chicken sub, and what the hell, I get 50% off my meal. Well, my manager gave me a free meal courtesy of him because he said I earned it after what happened the night before. I thought that was pretty considerate of him. He sometimes may be a lazy ass, but at least he is a kind and considerate lazy ass, and for that, I appreciate him.

And from now on, I'm only going to be driving European sports cars. I'm in love with my VDUB Golf. Later in life when I have the money, I'm getting an Audi. Ja ja ja! Wir fahr'n fahr'n fahr'n auf der Autobahn! fahr'n fahr'n fahr'n auf der Autobahn!

I'm counting down the days and hours for my departure from Austin to Harlingen. I took two days off from work--Friday and Saturday. I don't leave until very early Saturday morning, but my co-workers are supposed to think that I'm leaving Friday night, so sssssh. I'm looking foward to happy shopping times at Whole Foods Market and maybe, hopefully I could purchase a Macbook from the Apple store if they could draw up a monthly plan for me. Oh god, yesterday was an awkward time at work. I had to work with sanchita and she had to share with me that she needed tampons. So, she left me to work all by myself for a few minutes while she went to Dollar Tree to pick up some tamponitos. And then...my manager showed up to help his gurrrl clean up the store in his scrappy pajamas. The worse moment was when he was bent over sweeping under the toaster oven and I was trying to cross by to dump some sanitation buckets. His ass backed up into me with underwear lines, plumber's crack and all. I didn't need that..I didn't need that at all. Also, someone had the bright idea of purchasing a radio for the kitchen area. It plays Wild 104 24/7 ghetto booty jamz and it just adds another awful factor for me at work. I'm stuck with the radio and there is no way I could listen to anything that'll keep my sanity in check, because all radio stations in the Valley are horrible, sadly except NPR. I'd only be ridiculed for switching the radio to NPR because..no one else appreciates. Our regular customer, Ryan Wolf came by last night. He's actually a pretty nice and polite guy once you get the douche baggery he seems to portray on Channel 4 and his shrimpy stature. Mind you, he's shorter than me. He always orders the same damn bourbon chicken sub whenever he visits us and people think he's like a god or something whenever he is present. Funny thing is that whenever he walks in, we freak out and try to keep the store as clean as possible. It's like, "oh god, here comes the muthafuckin'foodpatrol!! clean something!!" After he ate, he left a pinche mess for me to clean. God, I can't wait until I'm out of work. I get paid tomorrow. Yeeahhh bitches!@

Ok, so I lied about having my pictures up on lj this weekend. I have pictures of my car on my camera but I need to upload them. Sooo..later in time, or maybe uhhh whenever I have the motivation to do so, I should have the pictures up sometime this week.

I have a cold/cough. My voice sounds like a 12 year old boy at the ripe stages of male puberty. :( :( :( :( No, no, no, I am not liking this one bit at all.

I'm at school right now trying to finish up some Spanish assignments at the computer lab and I'm fixing to high tail my ass out of here. Some dude was sitting right next to me a few minutes had a case of BO. My nose is stuffy, so the effect of the odor was diminished a bit, to say the least. 

I'm look forwarding to going home and eating some easy mac before I go into toasty hell and have to deal with the douche baggery of what is the archetype of an idiotic Quizno's customer. 

Now there is another guy right behind me who is talking unnecessarily loud about "sutures and shit". He made me lose my train of thought...aww shit.. 


Yeahh, I think I should be going home right about now.

I had a freak out session yesterday because I found out that I missed a test Tuesday. I missed a day from school because I was waiting around for the activation of my new car's insurance and I didn't want anything horrible to happen to my car. The poor baby was vulnerable. Sooo, I failed to show up for a chapter test and it tarnished my grade in psychology, but thankfully the professor let me make it up because I secretly obtained a doctor's excuse since my parents are really good friends with a doctor. Being good friends with doctors really pays off, y'know. So anyway, all of that stressing over my GPA getting the shits threw my immune system off guard and now I have a sore throat and cold. Well, shit.

Ok, I'll have pictures of my new car up in my journal this coming weekend. I promise. The car is very cute and very me.

I GOT A BRAND NEW CAR GOMGMOAGOMGAOUWE~~ SAGE GREEN VOLKSWAGEN RABBIT

shoyu ramen with nori! miam!

I need to get the hell away from this place and spend a few days in Austin. The monotonous schedule between going to TSTC and going into work is driving me insane. My dad wants to take us up there, but I don't know when...and then I have ask days off from work. I hate requesting days off because it means that I have to post a note up on a bulletin for my manager to see. Everyone else at work sees it and they tend to prod into why I requested the day off. None of your damn business, brown-nosing bitches! 

I feel drowsy. I don't know if it's the boring environment around me or if I'm just simply tired. The funny thing is that I'm in a library right now and I keep hearing a toilet flush...and I mean a very loud echoe-y flush. It's like a surreal moment in time. Or, it could be that the cleaning lady is cleaning the toilet with the restroom door open and every time she flushes the sound echoes throughout the library. Oh hell, I want to go home. I want ramen and I want tea. ='(

I'm going to go to HEB after school to pick up some Spaghetti-Os and ramen. =)
I really, really, really would like a macbook right about now.

Wow, today's such a gorgeous day. It's bright and sunny outside. The sky is clear, blue and beautiful, and the temperature is comfortable. This is a perfect day for a photographic spree. I'm glad I don't have to go into work because that would just shit on this wonderful day. 

I'm going to miss those tennis players since the tournament ended yesterday. This past week has been a hot, male foreigner extravaganza at Quizno's! I talked shortly with a Russian and Venuzuelan yesterday afternoon while at work. It was awesome. The Russian guy wasn't bad looking at all, either. He kinda, sorta reminded me of a Paul Bettany from Wimbledon. Cha--chiingngng!! 

I turned around to look out my window and I see two little lizards facing each other. They are having a little lizard conversation! It's so cute!

Well, working this week has had two benefits; I am getting paid very well because of all the hours I've been slaving this week and I've been having tall, hot European men as clientele. There's a tennis tournament in town! OMG Scandinavians and a Scotsman at my Quizno's?! My fantasy is coming true!! jajaja! 

I'm awake now. I want coffee and I want music.

Hello everyone! So, I made new account. I chose to make another one because I feel like starting fresh would prompt me to update often.

I recieved my packages from Japan yesterday and when I arrived home to find them sitting on my porch, I felt excited like a neurotic chihuahua. Here is what I recieved in my package:

anpan - Sweet bread filled with sweet red beans. I love this stuff!!!
Shigekix Super Ramune - These gummies are intensely sour at first, but taste like soda after a while. Yum!
yokan citron - A dense block of lemon flavored gelatin that is eaten with green tea. It's too sweet for my taste.
Konpeito- These are star shaped crystalized sugar balls. They're nice too look at, but the taste is nothing phenomenal. It's like eating bumpy sugar cubes.
Azuki red bean Kit-kats - These are great! One thing I really love about Japanese Kit-Kats is that their wafers are a lot much thicker than their American counterparts.
Kurogo Pocky - Awww, I love these! These are shortbread sticks coated with black sesame and other yummy stuff.
Green Tea Mousse Pocky - I haven't tried these yet, though I'm sure they are ass loads of awesomeness.

I haven't eaten all of my treats yet, but I've been tasting bits here and there. So far soo good.
